00:57:15,974 --> 00:57:19,726
we could show her presence
or her whereabouts

933
00:57:19,727 --> 00:57:21,896
at the time of the murder.

934
00:57:24,149 --> 00:57:28,152
During the search warrant,
we also searched Kaitlin's Jeep.

935
00:57:28,153 --> 00:57:32,031
I noticed that it had
an infotainment system installed in it.

936
00:57:32,866 --> 00:57:34,867
I checked with our digital forensics unit

937
00:57:34,868 --> 00:57:40,081
and asked them, "What type of information
would this infotainment system collect?"

938
00:57:40,748 --> 00:57:43,877
One of the things that they said
that it collected was track logs,

939
00:57:44,586 --> 00:57:46,253
your GPS data.

940
00:57:46,254 --> 00:57:50,174
We knew that the Jeep
was actually sold at CarMax.

941
00:57:50,175 --> 00:57:53,178
I went to CarMax and located the Jeep.

942
00:57:54,387 --> 00:57:58,974
{\an8}I researched on how
you pulled this device out

943
00:57:58,975 --> 00:58:01,101
{\an8}from various videos,

944
00:58:01,102 --> 00:58:03,103
and submitted it
to our digital forensics unit

945
00:58:03,104 --> 00:58:04,313
for them to process it

946
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:07,525
and see if there was
any data that was still on the device.

947
00:58:08,776 --> 00:58:11,820
Kaitlin had a pretty promising career.

948
00:58:11,821 --> 00:58:15,115
Colin actually described her
as being a financial guru,

949
00:58:15,116 --> 00:58:19,496
that she was in charge of all
of the financial aspects of their company.

950
00:58:19,996 --> 00:58:25,876
Colin had told me that he did provide
Kaitlin $40,000 to invest in the company.

951
00:58:25,877 --> 00:58:28,212
So we knew that Kaitlin was on the run

952
00:58:28,213 --> 00:58:31,424
with a significant amount of cash
available to her.

953
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:36,220
Kaitlin's one of those types of people

954
00:58:36,221 --> 00:58:40,433
that she gets an idea in her head
and she makes it happen.

955
00:58:43,520 --> 00:58:46,021
The U.S. Marshals were close to giving up

956
00:58:46,022 --> 00:58:48,023
because they couldn't find her.

957
00:58:48,024 --> 00:58:49,651
That was a scary thought to me.

958
00:58:53,196 --> 00:58:56,865
Based on her strong interest in yoga,

959
00:58:56,866 --> 00:59:01,328
they put out an ad in the town
where they thought she might be,

960
00:59:01,329 --> 00:59:03,665
seeking a yoga instructor.

961
00:59:08,169 --> 00:59:09,254
Amazingly,

962
00:59:10,421 --> 00:59:12,423
there was a response.

963
00:59:14,342 --> 00:59:15,969
They went to that location,

964
00:59:17,512 --> 00:59:18,513
and they saw her.

965
00:59:20,890 --> 00:59:24,269
Someone asked her
if she was Kaitlin Armstrong…

966
00:59:25,979 --> 00:59:27,605
and she said yes.

967
00:59:32,527 --> 00:59:35,195
I'm here to announce
that Kaitlin Armstrong

968
00:59:35,196 --> 00:59:37,614
{\an8}was captured on June 29th

969
00:59:37,615 --> 00:59:40,659
{\an8}by foreign officials
in the Republic of Costa Rica

970
00:59:40,660 --> 00:59:44,163
following a 43-day fugitive investigation.

971
00:59:47,041 --> 00:59:48,626
After she was arrested,

972
00:59:49,127 --> 00:59:53,298
we find out that she actually
went through plastic surgery,

973
00:59:53,798 --> 00:59:56,675
trying to make herself
look more like her sister.

974
00:59:56,676 --> 01:00:00,095
I think she just thought
she was smarter than everybody else

975
01:00:00,096 --> 01:00:01,764
and that she could get away with it.

976
01:00:06,269 --> 01:00:10,272
<i>Armstrong is now in custody
at the Travis County Jail.</i>

977
01:00:10,273 --> 01:00:14,902
<i>She's currently being held
under a $3.5 million bond.</i>

978
01:00:16,029 --> 01:00:18,572
Unfortunately, a lot of the information

979
01:00:18,573 --> 01:00:22,743
that's been presented so far in the media
is simply not accurate.

980
01:00:22,744 --> 01:00:26,496
{\an8}The police have a vested interest
in painting a picture

981
01:00:26,497 --> 01:00:29,666
{\an8}that supports
their initial assumptions and actions.

982
01:00:29,667 --> 01:00:33,170
We look forward
to this legal process ahead

983
01:00:33,171 --> 01:00:36,299
and these issues being heard
in a court of law.

984
01:00:39,636 --> 01:00:42,095
18, 19 days before trial,

985
01:00:42,096 --> 01:00:45,265
someone from the sheriff's office
called me and said,

986
01:00:45,266 --> 01:00:47,559
"Put your coffee down,
you won't believe this."

987
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:50,605
Kaitlin Armstrong escaped

988
01:00:51,189 --> 01:00:53,399
from the Travis County Jail.

989
01:00:53,983 --> 01:00:56,401
<i>Two deputies escorted Kaitlin Armstrong</i>

990
01:00:56,402 --> 01:00:58,487
<i>to a doctor's appointment
Wednesday morning.</i>

991
01:00:58,488 --> 01:01:03,075
She had this injury
that she could not have leg restraints on

992
01:01:03,076 --> 01:01:05,410
that required her
to go see an outside doctor.

993
01:01:05,411 --> 01:01:07,704
And so they allowed her to.

994
01:01:07,705 --> 01:01:10,416
The minute she left that doctor's office,
she booked it.

995
01:01:11,668 --> 01:01:14,837
{\an8}<i>Deputy chasing an inmate in the area.</i>

996
01:01:16,756 --> 01:01:18,298
We were hearing

997
01:01:18,299 --> 01:01:22,052
that she did start working out
excessively leading up to that,

998
01:01:22,053 --> 01:01:24,137
so there was definitely
some thought process

999
01:01:24,138 --> 01:01:25,473
that went into this escape.

1000
01:01:26,307 --> 01:01:32,480
She ran, and they apprehended her
about a mile down the road.

1001
01:01:33,815 --> 01:01:36,149
It was just even more evidence

1002
01:01:36,150 --> 01:01:40,445
that Kaitlin Armstrong really thought
she could get away with this.

1003
01:01:40,446 --> 01:01:43,407
And that she wasn't going
to have to answer for what she did

1004
01:01:43,408 --> 01:01:45,785
like anyone else might have to.

1005
01:01:56,254 --> 01:01:57,505
Oh, my gosh.

1006
01:02:05,763 --> 01:02:09,057
When I open drawers in her room,

1007
01:02:09,058 --> 01:02:11,393
I love picking things up

1008
01:02:11,394 --> 01:02:14,229
and just sticking them
in my face and smelling them.

1009
01:02:14,230 --> 01:02:17,233
And sometimes that makes me feel good,
and sometimes that makes me,

1010
01:02:17,900 --> 01:02:19,444
you know, feel sad too.

1011
01:02:22,739 --> 01:02:26,868
The more that I can be thankful
for the fact that…

1012
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:32,081
…that I, you know, that we had
Moriah here for 25 years…

1013
01:02:33,207 --> 01:02:35,667
…the more I can give thanks for that

1014
01:02:35,668 --> 01:02:38,963
and, um, and not focus on the loss.

1015
01:02:39,547 --> 01:02:40,757
And, um…

1016
01:02:41,716 --> 01:02:47,305
You know, it's not easy, though, because
I still want her to be here and, um…

1017
01:02:48,389 --> 01:02:50,308
…and I miss her.

1018
01:03:00,943 --> 01:03:02,027
{\an8}Moriah?

1019
01:03:02,028 --> 01:03:04,446
{\an8}Okay? Okay, Mommy?

1020
01:03:04,447 --> 01:03:06,615
{\an8}- Love you.
- Love you.

1021
01:03:06,616 --> 01:03:07,617
{\an8}Mm.

1022
01:03:09,035 --> 01:03:11,120
{\an8}Aw, that's a nice picture.

1023
01:03:12,705 --> 01:03:14,164
{\an8}Hi, everybody.

1024
01:03:14,165 --> 01:03:16,042
{\an8}Hi!

1025
01:03:37,396 --> 01:03:39,690
Grief is like a big mud puddle.

1026
01:03:40,983 --> 01:03:44,320
You can walk around it and around it.

1027
01:03:45,279 --> 01:03:48,157
Just be circling it
for the rest of your life.

1028
01:03:49,408 --> 01:03:52,328
Or you can walk right through it

1029
01:03:52,829 --> 01:03:54,705
and out the other end.

1030
01:04:02,797 --> 01:04:06,634
<i>A highly anticipated
murder trial gets underway here in Austin.</i>

1031
01:04:07,218 --> 01:04:11,888
<i>It's a case that has received
international media attention.</i>

1032
01:04:11,889 --> 01:04:15,183
There's a large contingency
of news reporters.

1033
01:04:15,184 --> 01:04:20,981
There's spectators, people tweeting live
the proceedings in the courtroom.

1034
01:04:20,982 --> 01:04:24,276
<i>Did Kaitlin Armstrong
shoot and kill Moriah Wilson?</i>

1035
01:04:24,277 --> 01:04:27,113
<i>That is a question
that a jury will answer.</i>

1036
01:04:27,697 --> 01:04:30,323
Sometimes when there's
no direct evidence, no eyewitness,

1037
01:04:30,324 --> 01:04:31,783
no video of the murder,

1038
01:04:31,784 --> 01:04:34,912
it's enough for a jury to hang
their hat on and acquit somebody.

1039
01:04:42,336 --> 01:04:45,256
Evidence will come out
that Kaitlin Armstrong

1040
01:04:45,965 --> 01:04:50,427
{\an8}was nowhere near the scene
of Miss Wilson's murder.

1041
01:04:50,428 --> 01:04:53,513
To the allegations
in paragraph one of the indictment,

1042
01:04:53,514 --> 01:04:54,639
how do you plead?

1043
01:04:54,640 --> 01:04:55,724
Not guilty.

1044
01:04:55,725 --> 01:04:58,518
To the allegations
to paragraph two of the indictment,

1045
01:04:58,519 --> 01:04:59,561
how do you plead?

1046
01:04:59,562 --> 01:05:00,478
Not guilty.

1047
01:05:00,479 --> 01:05:01,939
You may be seated.

1048
01:05:04,984 --> 01:05:11,866
We're going to start by giving you
information about three key players.

1049
01:05:14,368 --> 01:05:16,454
Number one will be Mo Wilson.

1050
01:05:18,456 --> 01:05:21,626
Second key player is Colin Strickland.

1051
01:05:22,251 --> 01:05:26,005
The third player is Kaitlin Armstrong,
the defendant,

1052
01:05:26,505 --> 01:05:28,048
who lived with Colin

1053
01:05:28,049 --> 01:05:31,677
in an on-again, off-again
romantic relationship.

1054
01:05:32,553 --> 01:05:34,888
Kaitlin Armstrong was not happy

1055
01:05:34,889 --> 01:05:37,308
with Colin still communicating

1056
01:05:38,809 --> 01:05:41,811
with Mo Wilson
after their romantic relationship ended.

1057
01:05:41,812 --> 01:05:47,193
What a wonderful and easy way
to paint a woman and to tell a story.

1058
01:05:47,860 --> 01:05:49,987
The woman scorned.

1059
01:05:50,947 --> 01:05:54,240
She had to be portrayed

1060
01:05:54,241 --> 01:05:57,954
as a jealous psycho to create the motive.

1061
01:05:59,497 --> 01:06:02,749
Mo was so young,
had so much life ahead of her.

1062
01:06:02,750 --> 01:06:06,003
My main thing was to hold
Kaitlin Armstrong accountable.

1063
01:06:07,004 --> 01:06:09,547
I was the second to take the stand.

1064
01:06:09,548 --> 01:06:12,425
All of a sudden, it's like,
"Get up, we're going in."

1065
01:06:12,426 --> 01:06:14,637
"We're swearing you in. It's starting."

1066
01:06:15,429 --> 01:06:19,474
There's no way to actually prepare you
for going into a situation like that,

1067
01:06:19,475 --> 01:06:20,850
where you're on the stand

1068
01:06:20,851 --> 01:06:23,646
facing Kaitlin Armstrong,
right there looking at you.

1069
01:06:25,481 --> 01:06:28,441
I just became hyper-focused.

1070
01:06:28,442 --> 01:06:31,820
I went into this, like, zone of,

1071
01:06:31,821 --> 01:06:35,615
"This is the most important thing
I could possibly do in my life."

1072
01:06:35,616 --> 01:06:37,742
"I want to see justice served,

1073
01:06:37,743 --> 01:06:42,665
and I want to do
my absolute best for my friend."

1074
01:06:43,666 --> 01:06:47,420
I fought for Mo
with everything I had that night.

1075
01:06:48,671 --> 01:06:53,466
From the moment that I got home,
I started doing chest compressions,

1076
01:06:53,467 --> 01:06:56,470
which was the longest ten minutes
of my entire life.

1077
01:06:57,972 --> 01:07:00,515
When I stepped down from the stand,

1078
01:07:00,516 --> 01:07:04,145
I looked Kaitlin Armstrong in the eyes,

1079
01:07:04,812 --> 01:07:06,522
and she showed nothing.

1080
01:07:07,273 --> 01:07:09,316
Absolutely nothing.

1081
01:07:12,278 --> 01:07:13,863
Hey, come here.

1082
01:07:17,908 --> 01:07:20,744
Somebody might be in here.
This might be the bike, okay?

1083
01:07:20,745 --> 01:07:21,911
Like-- Oh, look.

1084
01:07:21,912 --> 01:07:26,082
We had evidence
Kaitlin Armstrong drags Mo's bike

1085
01:07:26,083 --> 01:07:27,876
and throws it in the weeds.

1086
01:07:27,877 --> 01:07:29,295
Over there.

1087
01:07:30,296 --> 01:07:31,546
Okay, um…

1088
01:07:31,547 --> 01:07:33,716
432, I located the bike.

1089
01:07:36,135 --> 01:07:39,722
I don't know if she did that
just to thumb her nose at her,

1090
01:07:40,389 --> 01:07:42,767
or she was trying
to make it look like a robbery.

1091
01:07:44,435 --> 01:07:48,229
One of the hardest things
was when they rolled her bike in.

1092
01:07:48,230 --> 01:07:51,817
That… That kind of hit me,
seeing her bike.

1093
01:07:52,651 --> 01:07:54,195
Yeah, I remember it.

1094
01:07:55,696 --> 01:07:57,281
It was in the bag.

1095
01:07:59,450 --> 01:08:01,243
Oh…

1096
01:08:04,246 --> 01:08:05,915
That was her bike.

1097
01:08:06,415 --> 01:08:09,210
That was what she cared about.
That's what gave her joy.

1098
01:08:11,629 --> 01:08:13,630
When they recovered the bicycle,

1099
01:08:13,631 --> 01:08:17,467
they had processed it
for DNA and fingerprints.

1100
01:08:17,468 --> 01:08:21,554
I asked them to process
a couple other spots or items on the bike,

1101
01:08:21,555 --> 01:08:23,139
just to be sure.

1102
01:08:23,140 --> 01:08:26,309
We compared it with the DNA
that we collected from Kaitlin.

1103
01:08:26,310 --> 01:08:30,021
That comparison showed that Kaitlin's DNA

1104
01:08:30,022 --> 01:08:32,107
was actually on the bicycle.

1105
01:08:32,108 --> 01:08:37,237
The simplest, logical,
most reasonable explanation

1106
01:08:37,238 --> 01:08:40,240
for the defendant's DNA
to be on this bike?

1107
01:08:40,241 --> 01:08:43,368
The defendant touched the bike
after she exited.

1108
01:08:43,369 --> 01:08:46,205
She took the bike out,
and she threw it outside.

1109
01:08:46,997 --> 01:08:52,711
Every person that handled this bike
handled it in the same way.

1110
01:08:55,965 --> 01:09:02,263
I was very upset about the way
that Attorney Cofer handled the bike.

1111
01:09:02,763 --> 01:09:05,932
I didn't think that showed much respect.

1112
01:09:05,933 --> 01:09:08,853
And what's astounding, right here.

1113
01:09:09,478 --> 01:09:14,566
This was the area not swabbed for DNA.

1114
01:09:14,567 --> 01:09:19,446
What if it had shown
yet another unknown profile?

1115
01:09:27,454 --> 01:09:31,124
I mean, it's hard for all of us
to be in that room with Armstrong.

1116
01:09:31,125 --> 01:09:34,836
- And I think it's especially…
- Yeah.

1117
01:09:34,837 --> 01:09:37,672
I mean, it's hard for all of us, for sure.

1118
01:09:37,673 --> 01:09:41,176
- It feels cold in there. It's like…
- Yeah, it can be still.

1119
01:09:41,177 --> 01:09:44,179
I don't even feel that much
because I'm just like,

1120
01:09:44,180 --> 01:09:46,764
this just doesn't feel like a space

1121
01:09:46,765 --> 01:09:50,101
where I'm being encouraged
to feel anything.

1122
01:09:50,102 --> 01:09:54,063
Seeing her not show any emotion at all,

1123
01:09:54,064 --> 01:09:55,899
all I see is a stone.

1124
01:09:55,900 --> 01:09:57,818
When I look at her,
she looks like a stone.

1125
01:09:58,611 --> 01:10:02,489
Every once in a while,
I look and I just think, "Is there any…"

1126
01:10:03,407 --> 01:10:07,493
"Is there any softness
in that heart anywhere?"

1127
01:10:07,494 --> 01:10:10,915
"Is there any flesh in that heart,
or is it all stone?"

1128
01:10:11,415 --> 01:10:12,541
I don't know.

1129
01:10:15,753 --> 01:10:19,088
<i>Testimony on day three
of the Kaitlin Armstrong murder trial</i>

1130
01:10:19,089 --> 01:10:23,010
<i>with Colin Strickland,
Armstrong's then on-and-off boyfriend.</i>

1131
01:10:24,261 --> 01:10:28,807
It was hard to watch Colin
on the witness stand.

1132
01:10:30,017 --> 01:10:36,232
He did not look like the same person
in trial that he was before Moriah died.

1133
01:10:38,734 --> 01:10:42,362
It was hard to see Colin face-to-face.

1134
01:10:42,363 --> 01:10:45,198
Particularly because I placed
so much blame on him

1135
01:10:45,199 --> 01:10:49,911
for… his manipulation
of both Moriah and Kaitlin.

1136
01:10:49,912 --> 01:10:53,957
Colin Strickland gave many
noncommittal answers to attorneys today,

1137
01:10:53,958 --> 01:10:57,418
and also sat with his body
angled away and his hand up

1138
01:10:57,419 --> 01:11:00,047
in what may have been
an attempt to block out Armstrong.

1139
01:11:00,965 --> 01:11:02,383
His demeanor was,

1140
01:11:03,467 --> 01:11:05,093
"I do not want to be here."

1141
01:11:05,094 --> 01:11:06,469
He looked away.

1142
01:11:06,470 --> 01:11:08,263
He had his head down often.

1143
01:11:08,264 --> 01:11:10,598
He was slumped over the microphone.

1144
01:11:10,599 --> 01:11:13,101
He would put his hand
on his head like this.

1145
01:11:13,102 --> 01:11:15,019
His eyes were often closed,

1146
01:11:15,020 --> 01:11:18,523
and rarely would he look at the person
who was questioning him,

1147
01:11:18,524 --> 01:11:20,359
whether it was us or the other side.

1148
01:11:21,443 --> 01:11:25,113
When Colin was asked
in his cross-examinations

1149
01:11:25,114 --> 01:11:27,407
if he knew the defendant,

1150
01:11:27,408 --> 01:11:29,535
he actually came out and said, like, "No."

1151
01:11:30,911 --> 01:11:35,624
And I think it was a statement of,
"I thought I knew her, but I don't."

1152
01:11:36,292 --> 01:11:38,961
He had very pertinent information

1153
01:11:39,461 --> 01:11:43,006
to help us put this case together
to get justice for Mo.

1154
01:11:43,007 --> 01:11:44,842
And I didn't like the fact that…

1155
01:11:46,552 --> 01:11:49,095
he came off as being
very reluctant at times.

1156
01:11:49,096 --> 01:11:52,349
And I wanted to tell him, "Come on, dude."

1157
01:11:53,434 --> 01:11:56,520
"Do it like this
and make it easy on yourself."

1158
01:11:58,397 --> 01:12:01,107
<i>The state pulled up texts
between Strickland and Armstrong</i>

1159
01:12:01,108 --> 01:12:02,275
<i>from October 2021.</i>

1160
01:12:02,276 --> 01:12:05,862
<i>That was a time when Wilson
and Strickland met up in Austin.</i>

1161
01:12:05,863 --> 01:12:09,657
<i>The message that's seemingly
from Armstrong to Strickland,</i>

1162
01:12:09,658 --> 01:12:13,119
<i>"I know you better than to show up
at Meteor with that girl."</i>

1163
01:12:13,120 --> 01:12:16,665
<i>Strickland says "that girl"
is a reference to Wilson.</i>

1164
01:12:17,333 --> 01:12:19,709
<i>Jurors were shown
a text message sent to Strickland</i>

1165
01:12:19,710 --> 01:12:24,048
<i>containing a video at some kind
of firing range, shooting a gun.</i>

1166
01:12:24,715 --> 01:12:26,299
<i>The person's face isn't shown,</i>

1167
01:12:26,300 --> 01:12:29,762
<i>but Strickland testified
he believed it's Armstrong.</i>

1168
01:12:30,596 --> 01:12:34,641
Colin ended up in the middle
of some very unfortunate events.

1169
01:12:35,309 --> 01:12:38,436
I don't think that he ever anticipated

1170
01:12:38,437 --> 01:12:42,357
or intended for things
to happen the way that they did.

1171
01:12:42,358 --> 01:12:46,069
But I also don't think
that we can look at what happened

1172
01:12:46,070 --> 01:12:48,906
without acknowledging his involvement.

1173
01:12:51,158 --> 01:12:53,910
It bothers me that him lying

1174
01:12:53,911 --> 01:12:58,498
created the situation
and the scenario that led to Mo's death.

1175
01:12:58,499 --> 01:13:01,501
But on the other hand,
he didn't pull the trigger.

1176
01:13:01,502 --> 01:13:02,878
He didn't kill her.

1177
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:08,049
And there's nothing
about Kaitlin Armstrong, in my opinion,

1178
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:09,801
that suggested to Colin,

1179
01:13:09,802 --> 01:13:12,845
"I'd better be careful.
This girl could kill someone."

1180
01:13:12,846 --> 01:13:14,973
I don't think he saw it coming.

1181
01:13:15,474 --> 01:13:18,185
And if he did, maybe he'd have done
something different.

1182
01:13:23,982 --> 01:13:26,985
We wanted Pam Mazak
to be our final witness

1183
01:13:27,486 --> 01:13:30,822
to summarize the whole case, all the data,

1184
01:13:30,823 --> 01:13:34,159
and following it
in a chronological timeline.

1185
01:13:37,121 --> 01:13:38,621
From Colin's phone,

1186
01:13:38,622 --> 01:13:43,252
we realized he had Moriah
in his phone as Christine Wall.

1187
01:13:43,836 --> 01:13:47,547
Around 4:45, Colin's asking Moriah

1188
01:13:47,548 --> 01:13:51,217
if she'd like him to come
pick her up on the motorcycle.

1189
01:13:51,218 --> 01:13:55,680
Kaitlin did have access
to a lot of his information,

1190
01:13:55,681 --> 01:13:57,265
and there was an iPad at home,

1191
01:13:57,266 --> 01:14:01,519
and she more than likely would be able
to see all of this texting

1192
01:14:01,520 --> 01:14:03,856
between Colin and Moriah.

1193
01:14:06,608 --> 01:14:08,234
At around 4:49,

1194
01:14:08,235 --> 01:14:12,656
Moriah sends Colin
the address of where she's staying.

1195
01:14:13,157 --> 01:14:15,117
Now, it is under Christine Wall,

1196
01:14:16,076 --> 01:14:20,789
but Moriah sends a picture from her ride.

1197
01:14:21,790 --> 01:14:26,545
So, Kaitlin knows absolutely
that's who he's making plans with.

1198
01:14:29,214 --> 01:14:31,507
Kaitlin leaves the house,

1199
01:14:31,508 --> 01:14:34,595
and we believe she's got the gun with her.

1200
01:14:35,596 --> 01:14:39,766
She is heading up Lamar
towards the downtown area.

1201
01:14:40,976 --> 01:14:46,940
Then she takes a left
onto West 6th and heads west,

1202
01:14:47,524 --> 01:14:52,069
which would take you
to Deep Eddy, or that area.

1203
01:14:52,070 --> 01:14:57,034
But then, she turns around
and she starts heading east, onto 5th.

1204
01:14:57,784 --> 01:15:01,787
Then, her car takes a turn
around another block.

1205
01:15:01,788 --> 01:15:04,749
It's like she's trying
to figure out what to do.

1206
01:15:04,750 --> 01:15:09,338
And she pulls over into a parking lot area
and sits there for about a minute.

1207
01:15:10,047 --> 01:15:13,382
I don't know if initially
she was just going to go confront them.

1208
01:15:13,383 --> 01:15:17,512
A jealous person might, you know,
yell, scream, you know, slap, pull hair.

1209
01:15:17,513 --> 01:15:19,556
But that's not what happened.

1210
01:15:20,724 --> 01:15:25,479
She sits there for a minute and then makes
the decision to turn her phone off.

1211
01:15:26,897 --> 01:15:30,399
And then her Jeep starts heading east

1212
01:15:30,400 --> 01:15:33,111
and goes straight to Cash's neighborhood.

1213
01:15:35,322 --> 01:15:40,494
Kaitlin's Jeep locations match exactly
with all the surveillance video.

1214
01:15:42,788 --> 01:15:45,122
She's circling that neighborhood,

1215
01:15:45,123 --> 01:15:50,003
and she's sitting in her car and waiting
at about three different spots, at least.

1216
01:15:52,089 --> 01:15:56,092
We see Moriah and Colin heading back over.

1217
01:15:56,093 --> 01:15:58,470
Kaitlin's circling the block

1218
01:15:59,805 --> 01:16:02,391
until she sees them come home.

1219
01:16:08,981 --> 01:16:11,441
They're within a block of each other.

1220
01:16:12,276 --> 01:16:14,236
She's waiting for Colin to leave.

1221
01:16:17,864 --> 01:16:22,411
I know how it ends, and it's still
just really hard to watch this unfold.

1222
01:16:23,829 --> 01:16:26,414
One of the most horrific
things that we learned

1223
01:16:26,415 --> 01:16:31,711
was just how long
she had circled Cash's house.

1224
01:16:31,712 --> 01:16:33,589
Just how intentional it was.

1225
01:16:36,717 --> 01:16:39,636
She basically stalked her.

1226
01:16:41,597 --> 01:16:43,472
It was mind-blowing

1227
01:16:43,473 --> 01:16:46,350
just that we were able
to put all of that together

1228
01:16:46,351 --> 01:16:49,478
and that, really,
that-- that digital evidence

1229
01:16:49,479 --> 01:16:52,024
almost became
another witness in the trial.

1230
01:16:53,191 --> 01:16:57,571
You can't really accuse data of lying.

1231
01:16:58,947 --> 01:17:00,574
8:35, he drops her off.

1232
01:17:01,658 --> 01:17:02,909
Then Colin goes home.

1233
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:07,830
He does stop at 8:38 on MLK,

1234
01:17:07,831 --> 01:17:09,041
a few blocks

1235
01:17:10,000 --> 01:17:12,126
from dropping Mo off.

1236
01:17:12,127 --> 01:17:15,671
Then he texts Kaitlin
about the errand he was running.

1237
01:17:15,672 --> 01:17:16,965
Said, "Finished."

1238
01:17:17,466 --> 01:17:19,216
"Want to get something to eat?"

1239
01:17:19,217 --> 01:17:20,469
She doesn't respond.

1240
01:17:23,930 --> 01:17:27,558
As soon as he leaves,
she circles that alley.

1241
01:17:27,559 --> 01:17:29,810
She parks her Jeep.

1242
01:17:29,811 --> 01:17:32,564
And then she sits
in the Jeep for a little while.

1243
01:17:33,982 --> 01:17:35,608
Moriah unlocks the door.

1244
01:17:35,609 --> 01:17:37,109
She gets in.

1245
01:17:37,110 --> 01:17:43,532
And then she's, uh, texting
a podcaster around 9:13.

1246
01:17:43,533 --> 01:17:45,076
A few minutes later,

1247
01:17:45,077 --> 01:17:49,080
the… the screams
and the gunshots are heard.

1248
01:17:49,081 --> 01:17:51,583
Pow! Pow!

1249
01:17:52,709 --> 01:17:53,960
Two gunshots.

1250
01:17:55,295 --> 01:17:57,005
One to the front of the head.

1251
01:17:58,090 --> 01:18:00,049
One to the side of the head

1252
01:18:00,050 --> 01:18:03,345
that hits the index finger as it passes.

1253
01:18:04,888 --> 01:18:07,891
After four or five seconds of silence,

1254
01:18:08,642 --> 01:18:10,185
Kaitlin Armstrong

1255
01:18:10,852 --> 01:18:12,312
stood over Mo Wilson

1256
01:18:13,021 --> 01:18:14,564
and put a third shot

1257
01:18:15,107 --> 01:18:16,733
right in Mo Wilson's heart.

1258
01:18:18,777 --> 01:18:21,405
Hearing those screams, you know, they…

1259
01:18:22,239 --> 01:18:23,406
still bother me.

1260
01:18:23,407 --> 01:18:27,452
I try not to listen
to that one. It's-- It's very difficult.

1261
01:18:45,137 --> 01:18:47,304
I was coming to terms with,

1262
01:18:47,305 --> 01:18:49,224
"What if she's not put away?"

1263
01:18:50,058 --> 01:18:53,145
What does that mean for the Wilsons?
What does that mean for me?

1264
01:18:56,857 --> 01:19:00,944
I felt tense, nervous.

1265
01:19:02,696 --> 01:19:04,823
It's up to these 12 people.

1266
01:19:06,408 --> 01:19:11,871
Everything we do
all comes down to the jury.

1267
01:19:11,872 --> 01:19:14,081
If they didn't like it,
or they didn't buy it,

1268
01:19:14,082 --> 01:19:16,710
or even one of them didn't like it
or didn't buy it,

1269
01:19:17,294 --> 01:19:18,336
you're done.

1270
01:19:29,473 --> 01:19:31,349
The defendant will please rise.

1271
01:19:34,895 --> 01:19:39,774
In cause number D1DC22301129,

1272
01:19:39,775 --> 01:19:42,902
verdict of the jury
for the offense of murder,

1273
01:19:42,903 --> 01:19:46,155
we, the jury, having found
the defendant, Kaitlin Armstrong,

1274
01:19:46,156 --> 01:19:47,907
guilty of the offense of murder.

1275
01:19:47,908 --> 01:19:51,827
This court hereby
sentences you to 90 years

1276
01:19:51,828 --> 01:19:53,871
in the Texas Department
of Criminal Justice

1277
01:19:53,872 --> 01:19:57,750
and a $10,000 fine as imposed by the jury.

1278
01:19:57,751 --> 01:19:58,668
You may be seated.

1279
01:20:01,296 --> 01:20:03,798
Is there any allocution to be done?

1280
01:20:03,799 --> 01:20:05,008
Yes, Your Honor.

1281
01:20:16,770 --> 01:20:18,814
Kaitlin Armstrong.

1282
01:20:21,733 --> 01:20:25,319
I'm not sure if my words
can penetrate your heart,

1283
01:20:25,320 --> 01:20:26,738
but I'm gonna try.

1284
01:20:28,406 --> 01:20:31,034
I hate what you did
to my beautiful daughter.

1285
01:20:32,869 --> 01:20:35,622
It was very selfish and cowardly,

1286
01:20:36,331 --> 01:20:38,792
that violent act on May 11th.

1287
01:20:39,543 --> 01:20:41,253
It was cowardly

1288
01:20:42,045 --> 01:20:43,754
because you never chose

1289
01:20:43,755 --> 01:20:48,385
to face her woman to woman
in a civil conversation.

1290
01:20:49,094 --> 01:20:50,846
She would have listened.

1291
01:20:51,388 --> 01:20:53,682
She was an amazing listener.

1292
01:20:54,349 --> 01:20:56,935
She would have cared about your feelings.

1293
01:20:57,435 --> 01:21:00,230
She was a caring, empathetic person.

1294
01:21:00,939 --> 01:21:04,400
If you allowed yourself
to actually know her,

1295
01:21:04,401 --> 01:21:08,446
you never, ever would have
wanted to hurt her.

1296
01:21:09,739 --> 01:21:12,199
When you shot Moriah in the heart,

1297
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:15,245
you shot me in my heart.

1298
01:21:16,288 --> 01:21:20,250
You shot Eric and Matt in their hearts.

1299
01:21:26,882 --> 01:21:31,845
I don't know why God let this happen,
but He let it happen.

1300
01:21:33,471 --> 01:21:36,391
We trust that there's going
to be good come from it.

1301
01:21:40,478 --> 01:21:44,274
Maybe it'll help somebody,
you know, down the road…

1302
01:21:46,526 --> 01:21:48,695
so something like this doesn't happen.

1303
01:22:03,251 --> 01:22:05,170
There really are no winners here.

1304
01:22:06,212 --> 01:22:09,006
This is not a time for celebration,

1305
01:22:09,007 --> 01:22:10,592
but a time for prayer.

1306
01:22:11,801 --> 01:22:13,678
A time to pray for our family,

1307
01:22:14,346 --> 01:22:17,640
our friends, the Armstrong family,

1308
01:22:17,641 --> 01:22:18,642
and their friends.

1309
01:22:19,476 --> 01:22:21,894
This sad story is a perfect example

1310
01:22:21,895 --> 01:22:27,359
of why integrity and honesty are crucial
in our personal relationships.

1311
01:22:28,485 --> 01:22:32,989
{\an8}And how dishonesty can often lead
to unintended consequences.

1312
01:22:33,907 --> 01:22:39,704
Selfish manipulation, jealousy, and hatred
never lead to positive outcomes.

1313
01:22:40,789 --> 01:22:42,832
Violence is never a good way.

1314
01:22:43,416 --> 01:22:45,335
It only leads to more suffering.

1315
01:22:47,128 --> 01:22:49,130
Our lives are changed forever,

1316
01:22:50,131 --> 01:22:53,218
but with this challenging ordeal
now behind us,

1317
01:22:53,802 --> 01:22:58,014
we are ready to move forward
and continue our healing.

1318
01:22:59,349 --> 01:23:04,603
And we will do this
with Moriah's strong, determined,

1319
01:23:04,604 --> 01:23:06,940
gentle and kind spirit,

1320
01:23:07,607 --> 01:23:10,443
for we know
this is what she would want us to do.

1321
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:29,378
This is someone
that I'm sure most people in her life

1322
01:23:29,379 --> 01:23:32,089
couldn't have imagined her
doing something like this.

1323
01:23:32,090 --> 01:23:34,551
So it raises all these questions of, like,

1324
01:23:35,218 --> 01:23:37,261
"Do you ever really know anyone?"

1325
01:23:37,262 --> 01:23:39,513
"Am I capable
of doing something like that?"

1326
01:23:39,514 --> 01:23:41,683
"Is everyone capable
of doing something like that?"

1327
01:23:43,518 --> 01:23:48,273
This just is still so incomprehensible.

1328
01:23:49,232 --> 01:23:51,859
And when I do get angry,

1329
01:23:51,860 --> 01:23:53,235
all I can think of is,

1330
01:23:53,236 --> 01:23:57,282
"You stupid girl,
Kaitlin Armstrong, you stupid girl."

1331
01:23:57,991 --> 01:23:59,784
"Look what you did."

1332
01:24:17,927 --> 01:24:22,181
Kaitlin Armstrong took
so many things away from my sister.

1333
01:24:22,182 --> 01:24:23,975
She took away her life.

1334
01:24:24,476 --> 01:24:25,810
Her freedom.

1335
01:24:26,853 --> 01:24:29,814
Her ability to experience this world.

1336
01:24:30,315 --> 01:24:33,568
Her ability to feel joy.

1337
01:24:34,527 --> 01:24:38,363
The only just consequence for that

1338
01:24:38,364 --> 01:24:42,869
is that she should no longer be able
to have any of those experiences either,

1339
01:24:43,953 --> 01:24:45,455
for the rest of her life.

1340
01:25:09,979 --> 01:25:12,189
In my belief system,

1341
01:25:12,190 --> 01:25:16,944
whenever we make choices
and they have negative consequences,

1342
01:25:16,945 --> 01:25:19,447
we can't just walk away.

1343
01:25:20,740 --> 01:25:23,409
It's about what's right and wrong.

1344
01:25:25,286 --> 01:25:27,413
And being held accountable.

1345
01:25:32,252 --> 01:25:34,629
It was just such a senseless crime.

1346
01:26:05,410 --> 01:26:07,828
This is pretty much my life these days.

1347
01:26:07,829 --> 01:26:10,206
Just… time alone in the shop.

1348
01:26:12,709 --> 01:26:15,752
Part of that's just,
things are just outside of my control.

1349
01:26:15,753 --> 01:26:18,630
So I shrunk my world massively

1350
01:26:18,631 --> 01:26:21,216
so that it could feel
some kind of control.

1351
01:26:21,217 --> 01:26:24,304
Things are spinning out of…
out of control.

1352
01:26:32,228 --> 01:26:35,231
I regret everything.
I'm ashamed of everything I've done.

1353
01:26:37,275 --> 01:26:40,278
I would have never
fucking started bike racing.

1354
01:26:41,404 --> 01:26:43,364
Not ever met Kaitlin.

1355
01:26:44,324 --> 01:26:46,075
Not ever met Moriah.

1356
01:26:47,285 --> 01:26:50,872
Not ever… spoken with Moriah in private.

1357
01:26:52,498 --> 01:26:53,666
Every single thing.

1358
01:26:54,918 --> 01:26:56,544
Because it all led to this.

1359
01:27:10,266 --> 01:27:12,184
This is what I found in a thrift store

1360
01:27:12,185 --> 01:27:13,810
when I was trying to decide

1361
01:27:13,811 --> 01:27:18,148
whether or not I was going to be capable
of moving back into this space or not.

1362
01:27:18,149 --> 01:27:22,069
And I pulled it
out of a wall of 300 frames.

1363
01:27:22,070 --> 01:27:24,404
And it has a little bike
going out of the frame,

1364
01:27:24,405 --> 01:27:27,783
which feels really appropriate
for what was happening at the moment.

1365
01:27:27,784 --> 01:27:30,494
It's got a bloom over here,
so there's some hope going on.

1366
01:27:30,495 --> 01:27:33,372
Um, and then it says,
"With you all the way."

1367
01:27:33,373 --> 01:27:39,337
And I just kind of, um,
was totally overcome when I saw this.

1368
01:27:42,465 --> 01:27:43,632
When I moved back in,

1369
01:27:43,633 --> 01:27:47,761
I wanted this space
to feel joyful and bright.

1370
01:27:47,762 --> 01:27:50,681
And so I wanted there to be
a lot of color on the walls.

1371
01:27:50,682 --> 01:27:53,809
I wanted every single thing
I brought back into this home

1372
01:27:53,810 --> 01:27:55,979
to be intentional and to be joyful.

1373
01:27:57,689 --> 01:28:02,943
Everyone assumed that I would not
move back into my house.

1374
01:28:02,944 --> 01:28:07,281
My landlord, my dad, kept asking

1375
01:28:07,282 --> 01:28:09,908
if we needed to start moving my stuff out.

1376
01:28:09,909 --> 01:28:12,704
And I just was really reluctant.

1377
01:28:13,288 --> 01:28:15,456
I somehow felt

1378
01:28:16,499 --> 01:28:19,460
a strong connection there
and a strong pull.

1379
01:28:21,587 --> 01:28:23,297
When I look back at it,

1380
01:28:23,298 --> 01:28:25,924
the last day of her life
was really beautiful.

1381
01:28:25,925 --> 01:28:28,760
We laughed a lot together.

1382
01:28:28,761 --> 01:28:30,887
We made breakfast and coffee.

1383
01:28:30,888 --> 01:28:32,973
She went on a bike ride.

1384
01:28:32,974 --> 01:28:37,185
We talked about life and boys and family.

1385
01:28:37,186 --> 01:28:42,399
And it was a really beautiful last day.

1386
01:28:42,400 --> 01:28:44,485
And that feels sacred to me.

1387
01:28:45,570 --> 01:28:48,448
I want to safeguard that.

1388
01:28:49,949 --> 01:28:51,575
I feel her there.

1389
01:28:51,576 --> 01:28:54,620
I feel her joy there.

1390
01:28:55,413 --> 01:29:00,084
And I'm able to take that and harness it.

1391
01:29:00,793 --> 01:29:04,339
And I think she would be proud.
She'd be proud that I didn't just give up.

1392
01:29:12,555 --> 01:29:14,681
Growing up, going to Burke with Moriah,

1393
01:29:14,682 --> 01:29:16,017
and now coaching.

1394
01:29:16,601 --> 01:29:18,144
Alright, line up on the red line.

1395
01:29:19,228 --> 01:29:21,564
Being around the kids in this community

1396
01:29:22,482 --> 01:29:25,275
has been really healthy in a lot of ways.

1397
01:29:25,276 --> 01:29:28,195
Millie's to Trillium, to Magill,

1398
01:29:28,196 --> 01:29:30,490
to Moose Deuce, to Moriah's Ascent.

1399
01:29:31,908 --> 01:29:34,660
I do think
about what Mo would say quite often.

1400
01:29:36,287 --> 01:29:40,207
To get yourself
a little bit out of that hole,

1401
01:29:40,208 --> 01:29:43,586
she would tell me to get on my bike.

1402
01:29:45,463 --> 01:29:48,591
Just try to get
a little bit of momentum there.

1403
01:29:50,176 --> 01:29:53,137
And take it one step at a time.

1404
01:31:26,022 --> 01:31:29,066
Come on, Mo! Come on! Get up there!

1405
01:31:29,609 --> 01:31:31,068
Yeah, Mo!

1406
01:31:35,698 --> 01:31:38,283
Mo! Let's go, Mo!

1407
01:31:38,284 --> 01:31:41,287
Get up the hill! Dig it, Mo!

1408
01:31:41,913 --> 01:31:44,499
Go, go, go, go, go!

1409
01:32:43,099 --> 01:32:45,768
<i>If my senses fail</i>

1410
01:32:47,019 --> 01:32:50,814
<i>Meet me on the other side of paradise</i>

1411
01:32:50,815 --> 01:32:53,943
<i>Free from complications</i>

1412
01:32:54,694 --> 01:32:57,405
<i>Of our sense of time</i>

1413
01:32:58,531 --> 01:33:01,450
<i>Fill my windless sail</i>

1414
01:33:02,159 --> 01:33:05,996
<i>With broken echoes
Of a never-ending life</i>

1415
01:33:05,997 --> 01:33:09,125
<i>Whispered conversations</i>

1416
01:33:10,042 --> 01:33:13,754
<i>Twisted faces in the clouds</i>

1417
01:33:20,177 --> 01:33:24,432
<i>I've been hot-winged and hoodwinked
And dead on my feet</i>

1418
01:33:26,976 --> 01:33:31,063
<i>The sound and the fury remain over me</i>

1419
01:33:33,733 --> 01:33:37,652
<i>And all of the footprints
That fall in a line</i>

1420
01:33:37,653 --> 01:33:43,326
<i>Were our common ancestors
Wandering hills in the night</i>

1421
01:33:46,287 --> 01:33:49,874
<i>If my senses fail</i>

1422
01:33:50,374 --> 01:33:54,210
<i>Meet me on the other side of paradise</i>

1423
